1
00:00:00,090 --> 00:00:02,160
- What's the laziest way for beginners

2
00:00:02,160 --> 00:00:03,360
to make money online?
(cash register chimes)

3
00:00:03,360 --> 00:00:05,940
That's one of the most
common questions I get asked,

4
00:00:05,940 --> 00:00:08,580
and honestly, who doesn't
wanna make good money

5
00:00:08,580 --> 00:00:10,980
with minimal effort, all
while having the freedom

6
00:00:10,980 --> 00:00:12,810
to work from anywhere in the world?

7
00:00:12,810 --> 00:00:15,660
So as a millionaire businessman,
I'm gonna use my knowledge

8
00:00:15,660 --> 00:00:17,790
to finally answer this question.

9
00:00:17,790 --> 00:00:20,610
As you can see, I've got
this grid out in front of me.

10
00:00:20,610 --> 00:00:22,140
We're gonna use it to figure out

11
00:00:22,140 --> 00:00:25,680
which online moneymaking
method is truly the laziest

12
00:00:25,680 --> 00:00:28,620
by judging each one in five categories.

13
00:00:28,620 --> 00:00:30,780
First up, learning curve.

14
00:00:30,780 --> 00:00:31,860
This is how long it takes

15
00:00:31,860 --> 00:00:33,600
before you're earning decent money.

16
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:36,480
Ideally, we want this to
be as short as possible

17
00:00:36,480 --> 00:00:38,370
to keep things truly lazy.

18
00:00:38,370 --> 00:00:39,750
Next up

19
00:00:39,750 --> 00:00:41,010
is fulfillment.

20
00:00:41,010 --> 00:00:43,980
This is all about delivering
whatever it is you're selling,

21
00:00:43,980 --> 00:00:46,350
and we want this to be
as simple as possible.

22
00:00:46,350 --> 00:00:48,750
Then there's scalability.

23
00:00:48,750 --> 00:00:51,390
This measures how easy you
can grow and make more money

24
00:00:51,390 --> 00:00:53,790
without piling on extra work.

25
00:00:53,790 --> 00:00:56,910
After that, we have startup capital

26
00:00:56,910 --> 00:00:58,470
or how much money you'll need

27
00:00:58,470 --> 00:01:00,630
to invest upfront to get going.

28
00:01:00,630 --> 00:01:03,990
And finally we're looking at risk level.

29
00:01:03,990 --> 00:01:06,240
Higher risk usually means more stress,

30
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:09,510
which even if it's easy money
can drain you over time.

31
00:01:09,510 --> 00:01:12,210
Today I am only gonna be
covering money making methods

32
00:01:12,210 --> 00:01:13,920
that can realistically bring you in

33
00:01:13,920 --> 00:01:15,810
over $100 a day.
(cash register chimes)

34
00:01:15,810 --> 00:01:19,260
So, no online surveys
or transcription sites.

35
00:01:19,260 --> 00:01:20,460
They pay next to nothing

36
00:01:20,460 --> 00:01:22,680
and just end up wasting your time anyway.

37
00:01:22,680 --> 00:01:24,810
Method one, freelancing.

38
00:01:24,810 --> 00:01:27,810
This is all about using your
skills to earn money online

39
00:01:27,810 --> 00:01:30,000
by working directly with clients.

40
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,010
There are tons of skills
you can choose from,

41
00:01:32,010 --> 00:01:35,130
including video editing,
social media management,

42
00:01:35,130 --> 00:01:38,370
graphic design, copywriting,
and website development.

43
00:01:38,370 --> 00:01:40,950
This is great 'cause you
get to choose your projects

44
00:01:40,950 --> 00:01:44,130
and work schedule, which gives
you a lot of flexibility,

45
00:01:44,130 --> 00:01:45,990
so it's perfect for those wanting control

46
00:01:45,990 --> 00:01:47,610
over when and where they work.

47
00:01:47,610 --> 00:01:51,450
In my opinion, the best one
to focus on is video editing,

48
00:01:51,450 --> 00:01:53,610
as due to the rise of digital content,

49
00:01:53,610 --> 00:01:56,460
there's a real shortage of
great editors at the moment.

50
00:01:56,460 --> 00:02:00,060
But the real question is,
how lazy is freelancing?

51
00:02:00,060 --> 00:02:01,530
Well, let's have a look.

52
00:02:01,530 --> 00:02:05,310
For learning curve, I'm
gonna say six months.

53
00:02:05,310 --> 00:02:07,500
To start making good
money, you'll probably need

54
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:11,100
at least this amount of time
to learn and build a portfolio.

55
00:02:11,100 --> 00:02:14,070
The most popular skills
like video editing, design,

56
00:02:14,070 --> 00:02:17,580
and copywriting have tons
of tutorials on YouTube,

57
00:02:17,580 --> 00:02:19,950
which can help you level up very quickly.

58
00:02:19,950 --> 00:02:23,100
For fulfillment, I'm gonna
say this is pretty hard.

59
00:02:23,100 --> 00:02:26,220
Dealing with clients
one-on-one can be a bit tricky.

60
00:02:26,220 --> 00:02:29,730
I remember when my son was
freelancing as a video editor.

61
00:02:29,730 --> 00:02:31,980
Every week he'd be venting about a client

62
00:02:31,980 --> 00:02:33,840
who kept requesting changes

63
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:36,270
that he felt made the video worse.

64
00:02:36,270 --> 00:02:38,190
It was so frustrating for him

65
00:02:38,190 --> 00:02:39,960
because they just didn't get it,

66
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:41,340
but he had to keep his cool,

67
00:02:41,340 --> 00:02:43,680
play nice, and make those changes anyway.

68
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:44,730
It's tough to do,

69
00:02:44,730 --> 00:02:47,070
especially when you're
passionate about a project

70
00:02:47,070 --> 00:02:49,260
and feel like someone is dragging it down.

71
00:02:49,260 --> 00:02:50,940
Now, for scalability,

72
00:02:50,940 --> 00:02:54,420
I'm gonna say this one is pretty limited.

73
00:02:54,420 --> 00:02:58,290
In freelancing, your income
is tied directly to your time.

74
00:02:58,290 --> 00:03:00,330
This means there's a cap on your earnings,

75
00:03:00,330 --> 00:03:01,950
unless you either charge higher rates

76
00:03:01,950 --> 00:03:04,260
or hire other people
to do the work for you.

77
00:03:04,260 --> 00:03:07,680
The only way to scale is to
build a good client base,

78
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:09,720
as this will lead to steady work.

79
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:13,289
You can do this on freelance
sites like Upwork and Fiverr.

80
00:03:13,289 --> 00:03:15,750
Fiverr is ideal for beginners,
as you can list services

81
00:03:15,750 --> 00:03:17,910
without needing to bid on jobs.

82
00:03:17,910 --> 00:03:20,220
Upwork might be a bit more competitive,

83
00:03:20,220 --> 00:03:22,590
but it often has higher paying projects.

84
00:03:22,590 --> 00:03:25,710
Startup capital, though, is pretty good.

85
00:03:25,710 --> 00:03:27,540
It's practically zero.

86
00:03:27,540 --> 00:03:30,180
If you already have a
computer and internet access,

87
00:03:30,180 --> 00:03:31,500
you're nearly set.

88
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:33,750
Some tools, like the Adobe Creative Suite

89
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:37,260
for design or video editing,
can be a great investment,

90
00:03:37,260 --> 00:03:40,680
but there are free or low-cost
alternatives like Canva

91
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:42,360
that you get started with.

92
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:44,820
Your biggest investment here is your time.

93
00:03:44,820 --> 00:03:47,640
Finally, for risk, this is pretty low,

94
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:50,460
mainly because there is
very little upfront cost

95
00:03:50,460 --> 00:03:53,100
and you're directly paid for each project.

96
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:56,580
The only real risk is
potentially inconsistent income,

97
00:03:56,580 --> 00:03:59,040
so you might have to put
in some effort initially

98
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:01,530
to build up a steady stream of clients.

99
00:04:01,530 --> 00:04:05,010
So overall, this is definitely
not the laziest method.

100
00:04:05,010 --> 00:04:07,290
However, freelancing could be a great way

101
00:04:07,290 --> 00:04:10,290
to start making money online,
especially if you're willing

102
00:04:10,290 --> 00:04:13,830
to put in the time, build up
your skills and a client list.

103
00:04:13,830 --> 00:04:16,320
Method two, Airbnb arbitrage.

104
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:19,500
This is a moneymaking method
where you rent out a property

105
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:23,040
on a long-term lease, and
then rent it out short-term

106
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:25,080
on platforms like Airbnb.

107
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:27,720
Essentially, you're
acting as the middle man,

108
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:29,820
taking advantage of the price difference

109
00:04:29,820 --> 00:04:31,590
between your long-term lease

110
00:04:31,590 --> 00:04:33,540
and the short term rental rates.

111
00:04:33,540 --> 00:04:36,390
This could be a great way
to generate passive income

112
00:04:36,390 --> 00:04:38,460
without having to own
the property yourself.

113
00:04:38,460 --> 00:04:40,410
You'll need to get
permission from the owner,

114
00:04:40,410 --> 00:04:41,340
but you'd be surprised

115
00:04:41,340 --> 00:04:43,620
how many landlords are okay with this.

116
00:04:43,620 --> 00:04:46,380
They either don't know
how to operate an Airbnb

117
00:04:46,380 --> 00:04:48,990
or don't have the time
to do it themselves.

118
00:04:48,990 --> 00:04:50,760
So, how lazy is it?

119
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:55,440
This one has a one to
three-month learning curve.

120
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:59,100
Getting the hang of Airbnb
arbitrage doesn't take too long.

121
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:02,190
You need to spend a bit of time
learning about the platform,

122
00:05:02,190 --> 00:05:04,350
understanding local rental laws,

123
00:05:04,350 --> 00:05:06,900
and getting familiar
with property management.

124
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:08,700
The bulk of this preparation time

125
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:11,010
will be spent finding good properties.

126
00:05:11,010 --> 00:05:14,610
Look for places near tourist
attractions, universities,

127
00:05:14,610 --> 00:05:16,200
or business districts.

128
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:18,810
Websites like AirDNA can give you insights

129
00:05:18,810 --> 00:05:21,420
into rental prices and occupancy rates.

130
00:05:21,420 --> 00:05:23,700
You'd also need to reach
out to the landlords

131
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:27,420
and let them know you plan to
sublet the property on Airbnb.

132
00:05:27,420 --> 00:05:30,120
Make sure you get their
permission in writing,

133
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:32,040
as you don't want 'em to find out later

134
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:33,210
and cancel your lease

135
00:05:33,210 --> 00:05:35,100
after you've put in all that hard work

136
00:05:35,100 --> 00:05:37,350
getting it up and running on Airbnb.

137
00:05:37,350 --> 00:05:39,520
Fulfillment is medium

138
00:05:40,650 --> 00:05:41,580
difficulty.

139
00:05:41,580 --> 00:05:44,970
While it can be a relatively
hands-off way of making money,

140
00:05:44,970 --> 00:05:47,250
you still have to deal
with some customer issues

141
00:05:47,250 --> 00:05:48,630
from time-to-time.

142
00:05:48,630 --> 00:05:50,820
Guests might have questions or concerns,

143
00:05:50,820 --> 00:05:53,070
and you'll need to manage
check-ins and cleaning.

144
00:05:53,070 --> 00:05:55,650
It's not as easy as just
putting up a listing

145
00:05:55,650 --> 00:05:58,890
and forgetting about it,
but it can be manageable

146
00:05:58,890 --> 00:06:00,510
with a good system in place.

147
00:06:00,510 --> 00:06:03,330
That's why it's a good idea
to use management software

148
00:06:03,330 --> 00:06:06,720
like Guesty or Hostfully to
streamline your bookings,

149
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:08,970
communication, and check-ins.

150
00:06:08,970 --> 00:06:11,790
This will save you time and
help keep your guests happy.

151
00:06:11,790 --> 00:06:14,550
Now, here's where it gets really exciting,

152
00:06:14,550 --> 00:06:18,840
because scalability is very high.

153
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:21,690
One of the best parts
about Airbnb arbitrage

154
00:06:21,690 --> 00:06:23,730
is that it's highly scalable.

155
00:06:23,730 --> 00:06:26,670
You can keep adding more
properties to your portfolio

156
00:06:26,670 --> 00:06:30,600
and there's really no limit
to how many you can manage.

157
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:33,180
You just have to make sure you
have the time and resources

158
00:06:33,180 --> 00:06:35,190
to keep everything running smoothly.

159
00:06:35,190 --> 00:06:36,960
Here's the bad news, though.

160
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:39,910
This is gonna require 5K

161
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:44,730
to 15K of startup capital.

162
00:06:44,730 --> 00:06:46,890
This is where it gets a bit tricky.

163
00:06:46,890 --> 00:06:49,320
You'll need a decent
amount of upfront cash

164
00:06:49,320 --> 00:06:52,680
to secure a lease, cover any
initial furnishing costs,

165
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:55,080
and possibly pay for cleaning services.

166
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:58,170
Finally, risk level is pretty high.

167
00:06:58,170 --> 00:07:01,170
The main downside to this
method is the upfront cash

168
00:07:01,170 --> 00:07:02,310
you need to invest.

169
00:07:02,310 --> 00:07:05,190
However, if you take advantage
of the management tools

170
00:07:05,190 --> 00:07:08,370
I mentioned, it can be
relatively hands-off.

171
00:07:08,370 --> 00:07:12,180
Saying that, I reckon we can
find an even lazier option.

172
00:07:12,180 --> 00:07:13,890
Method three,

173
00:07:13,890 --> 00:07:15,270
an eBay shop.

174
00:07:15,270 --> 00:07:17,010
This is a great way to make money

175
00:07:17,010 --> 00:07:18,840
by selling products online.

176
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:22,140
You can sell anything from
vintage clothing and electronics

177
00:07:22,140 --> 00:07:26,400
to handmade items or even get
rid of stuff you don't need.

178
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:30,030
With millions of users, eBay
offers a massive marketplace

179
00:07:30,030 --> 00:07:32,940
where you can reach potential
buyers without needing

180
00:07:32,940 --> 00:07:34,980
to set up an actual shop in the street.

181
00:07:34,980 --> 00:07:37,710
But the question is, how lazy is it?

182
00:07:37,710 --> 00:07:39,480
Well, we're gonna find out.

183
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:44,220
The learning curve for this
is around about two weeks.

184
00:07:44,220 --> 00:07:47,130
Getting started with eBay
is pretty straightforward.

185
00:07:47,130 --> 00:07:48,390
Before diving in,

186
00:07:48,390 --> 00:07:51,120
think about what kind of
products you want to sell.

187
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:53,700
Are you into vintage
clothing, collectibles,

188
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:55,980
electronics, or something else?

189
00:07:55,980 --> 00:07:58,200
You can then use eBay's search function

190
00:07:58,200 --> 00:08:01,830
to see what's popular and in
demand in your chosen niche.

191
00:08:01,830 --> 00:08:04,500
Then you just need to create
your eBay seller account

192
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:05,970
and source your products.

193
00:08:05,970 --> 00:08:08,250
As I mentioned before,
you can start with things

194
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:10,170
in your house that you don't want anymore,

195
00:08:10,170 --> 00:08:11,790
or you could order items you've seen

196
00:08:11,790 --> 00:08:14,010
selling on eBay from DHgate.

197
00:08:14,010 --> 00:08:17,280
This process shouldn't take
more than a couple of weeks.

198
00:08:17,280 --> 00:08:21,660
For fulfillment, I'm gonna say
this is a medium difficulty.

199
00:08:21,660 --> 00:08:23,910
You'll have to send your
products out yourself

200
00:08:23,910 --> 00:08:25,980
and you might run into
some customer issues

201
00:08:25,980 --> 00:08:29,790
from time-to-time, like returns
or inquiries about products.

202
00:08:29,790 --> 00:08:32,340
I've been running my
eBay shops for years now,

203
00:08:32,340 --> 00:08:33,510
and in my experience,

204
00:08:33,510 --> 00:08:37,230
it's always better to send a
replacement or issue a refund,

205
00:08:37,230 --> 00:08:40,230
even if you suspect the
customer is trying to scam you.

206
00:08:40,230 --> 00:08:41,160
It's simply better

207
00:08:41,160 --> 00:08:43,500
to keep your eBay
account in good standing.

208
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:44,970
These kinds of situations

209
00:08:44,970 --> 00:08:47,250
used to stress me out something rotten.

210
00:08:47,250 --> 00:08:49,560
However, now I've learned
it's just the cost

211
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:52,650
of selling items online and
there's no getting away from it.

212
00:08:52,650 --> 00:08:56,130
The scalability of this one is very high.

213
00:08:56,130 --> 00:08:58,140
You can continually add new products

214
00:08:58,140 --> 00:09:01,260
and there's really no limit to
how many items you can sell.

215
00:09:01,260 --> 00:09:02,880
As you start to make more money,

216
00:09:02,880 --> 00:09:04,980
you might even want to
consider branching out

217
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:07,770
onto other platforms like Etsy and Amazon.

218
00:09:07,770 --> 00:09:11,070
Alternatively, you could
start various eBay shops

219
00:09:11,070 --> 00:09:12,450
in different niches.

220
00:09:12,450 --> 00:09:17,450
I'd say you need at least
$500 of startup capital.

221
00:09:17,790 --> 00:09:19,290
To get your shop off the ground,

222
00:09:19,290 --> 00:09:21,810
you'll need to use this
initial money for stock

223
00:09:21,810 --> 00:09:23,617
depending on what you want to sell.

224
00:09:23,617 --> 00:09:27,000
$500 can be a reasonable starting point.

225
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,180
You can find good deals at
thrift stores, garage sales,

226
00:09:30,180 --> 00:09:32,820
or even wholesale suppliers like DHgate,

227
00:09:32,820 --> 00:09:34,050
who I mentioned earlier.

228
00:09:34,050 --> 00:09:35,170
I'd say this is

229
00:09:36,300 --> 00:09:37,380
medium risk.

230
00:09:37,380 --> 00:09:39,780
This risk comes from the fact
that you're putting money

231
00:09:39,780 --> 00:09:42,420
into stock that might not sell right away.

232
00:09:42,420 --> 00:09:45,000
However, if you're
smart about your choices

233
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:48,510
and stay on top of trends, you
can really reduce that risk.

234
00:09:48,510 --> 00:09:51,600
I'd say the eBay shop
method is winning so far,

235
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:54,150
as it's a pretty lazy money making method.

236
00:09:54,150 --> 00:09:56,820
However, it's lacking in
a few of the categories,

237
00:09:56,820 --> 00:09:58,410
so let's keep going.

238
00:09:58,410 --> 00:10:02,010
Method four, affiliate marketing.

239
00:10:02,010 --> 00:10:03,660
This is a great way to earn money

240
00:10:03,660 --> 00:10:07,110
by promoting other people's
products or services.

241
00:10:07,110 --> 00:10:09,690
You get paid a commission
for every sale made

242
00:10:09,690 --> 00:10:11,340
through your referral link.

243
00:10:11,340 --> 00:10:12,660
It's a win-win.

244
00:10:12,660 --> 00:10:14,460
You help someone sell their products

245
00:10:14,460 --> 00:10:17,070
while earning a little
something for yourself.

246
00:10:17,070 --> 00:10:20,370
No need to handle products
or do any customer service.

247
00:10:20,370 --> 00:10:23,910
So let's see how this stacks
up against the other methods.

248
00:10:23,910 --> 00:10:26,340
The learning curve for
this one is super short,

249
00:10:26,340 --> 00:10:29,430
I'd say one to two days.

250
00:10:29,430 --> 00:10:31,380
All you really need to do is to sign up

251
00:10:31,380 --> 00:10:33,390
to different affiliate programs.

252
00:10:33,390 --> 00:10:36,540
You can use sites like
Amazon Associates, ClickBank,

253
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:38,340
and my favorite, Impact.

254
00:10:38,340 --> 00:10:40,110
